change.subject: Getting ES3 back up to speed

change-plan.description: Exchange Server 3 has gone down due to a CPU spike
change-plan.description-html:
1.Backup existing information from the old server
2.Setup the new server with Windows Server 2008
3.Install Exchange Server and configure it
4.Import data from the backup and get the server up and running.

change-reason.description: Exchange Server 3 has gone down due to a CPU spike. Rebooting doesn’t solve the problem.
change-reason.description-html: Exchange Server 3 has gone down due to a CPU spike. Rebooting doesn’t solve the problem.

change-body.description-html:
Hi Team,

One of our email servers, Exchange Server (ES3) has been acting up. We tried rebooting it, but that didn’t help. We need to get it replaced ASAP.

Regards
Rachel

backout-plan.description: Connectivity is made one link at a time. A verification of administrative connectivity to the 7100 switch and core is performed after each connection, Should issues occur, we can easily roll back one step since each step is checked as we progressed.
backout-plan.description-html: Connectivity is made one link at a time.  A verification of administrative connectivity to the 7100 switch and core is performed after each connection,  Should issues occur, we can easily roll back one step since each step is checked as we progressed.

change-body.description:
Issue to resolve: With the current network setup, we can not bring up the new Dell server chassis, since this creates switching loop.
A new network reconfiguration is required to prevent this physical loop so the new Dell server chassis can function properly. The changes also simplify the connections to allow for easier identification of issues in the future.
change-body.description-html:
Issue to resolve: With the current network setup, we can not bring up the new Dell server chassis, since this creates switching loop.

A new network reconfiguration is required to prevent this physical loop so the new Dell server chassis can function properly. The changes also simplify the connections to allow for easier identification of issues in the future.

custom_field.test_plan_14966: After the connections are in place, we will test all connectivity to the servers and verify that the SAN is online and functioning properly.
custom_field.backout_plan_14966: All device settings are backed up. Current connections are labeled and documented. Should issues occur, we can revert back to the current configuration and retest all connections to ensure connectivity.

change.subject: Upgrade to PowerFAIDS Release 21.4, Net Partner Release 21.4, and Web Client Release 21.4

change-impact.description: PowerFAIDS, Net Partner (myfinancialaid.msoe.edu), and web client will be down. This will affect PowerFAIDS users and all students.
change-impact.description-html: PowerFAIDS, Net Partner (myfinancialaid.msoe.edu), and web client will be down. This will affect PowerFAIDS users and all students.

change-reason.description:
New releases are available. PowerFAIDS 21.4 includes: • 2017/2018 Parameter Roll Forward • 2017/2018 CommonLine Loan processing • 2017/2018 Disbursement Authorization • 2017/2018 Disbursement Authorization Reconciliation • 2017/2018 External Award Import • 2017/2018 External Disbursement Import • 2017/2018 IDOC Submission • Direct Loan Fee increases • Student Migration • Modified Pell behavior • U.S. Department of Education’s Fiscal Operations Report for 2015/2016 and Application to Participate for 2017/2018 • Liaison Committee on Medical Education • CCC-MIS Report • Enhanced Other Years Screen Functionality • Projection Reporting using point in time data • Reconcile Student Data for updated POE and Fund parameters • Awarding Estimated Funds • Document Management across Multiple Years • Global Comments
PowerFAIDS 21.4 includes several background enhancements to capture point in time data to assist you with projection reporting due to Early FAFSA and Prior Prior Year processing in 2017/2018. As part of this release we have developed a custom report, Projection Reporting which can be downloaded from the PowerFAIDS Resource Center>Downloads>Custom Reports. You can import, modify and use this report format based on your institutions need for projection reporting or using the mnemonics created in this release create your own projection report.
Net Partner 21.4 includes: • Support for customizable Financial Aid Disclosure • Estimated Awards Identifier
Web Client 21.4 includes: • Global Comments display • Estimated Awards display
